5 Do's and 5 Don'ts for responsible social media use as a college student.

✅ Responsible Social Media Use – Checklist 
✔️ Do’s
•	Maintain a professional and positive online presence 
•	Follow credible sources for news and information 
•	Use two-factor authentication for better account security 
•	Be respectful while commenting or interacting with others 
•	Limit screen time and use social media productively 

_______________________________________________

❌ Don’ts
•	Don’t accept friend requests from unknown people 
•	Avoid sharing unverified news or rumours 
•	Don’t post content that can harm your reputation 
•	Avoid using public Wi-Fi for logging into personal accounts 
•	Don’t get addicted to social media or let it affect your studies


